Hard

Use ipywidgets to create interactive controls

In[35]:
import ipywidgets as widgets

This widget will allow the user to adjust the starting angle of the pie chart

In[36]:
#source: https://ipywidgets.readthedocs.io/en/stable/examples/Using%20Interact.html
#source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wb6k_T4rKBQ&t=22s
def hpww_widget(start_angle=90):
    hpww_cat.plot(kind='pie', startangle=start_angle, counterclock=False, labels=None)
    plt.ylabel('')
    plt.title('Hours Worked Per Week')
    plt.legend(labels=hpww_cat.index, loc="lower right", bbox_to_anchor=(1.5, 0.25), title="Legend")
    plt.show()
In[37]:
widgets.interact(hpww_widget, start_angle=10)

interactive(children=(IntSlider(value=10, description='start_angle', max=30, min=-10), Output()), _dom_classes
Out[37]:
<function __main__.hpww_widget(start_angle=90)>
